Message: 695884

From: Karavas Kostas (ops@astraship.com)

Subject: M/V THALASSINI | VOY.51 | SUEZ CANAL TRANSIT

Date: April 25th 2025, 17:36:13

To: ops@gssshipping-eg.com, suezcanal@gssshipping-eg.com

Cc: greece@gssshipping-eg.com

 

Dear Tatiana / Tamer,

Good day.

 

REF: M/V THALASSINI // VOY.51 // SUEZ CANAL TRANSIT // ETA 01-MAY-25, AGW/WP

 

We are sending you from Astra Shipmanagement Inc., a ship management company based in Voula, Athens, Greece.  The under our management subject vessel is estimated to arrive at the above mentioned port/date.

In respect of this, we would be grateful to receive your reply/information on our followings and advise your most competitive Agency Fee:


1- Your full style, tel-fax numbers, e-mail address // Name of p.i.c. with mobile and aoh phone nr. in case of emergency.

2- Availability and related expenses for fresh water supply.

3- Availability of reception facilities for sludge/oily water/wash water/sewage/garbage, cost per cbm or ton and procedures for ordering such operation. Please advise if any disposal is compulsory. In addition to this, kindly advise whether the providers are ISO14001 approved.

 

4- Whether crew changes can be done and if so, VISA/ COV-19 requirements for Greek and Filipino seamen:
Kindly advise the ff:
A) closest/ most convenient airport
B) the estimated cost for visa/ man
C) the handling fees for crew change/ man (if any)
D) the estimated expenses for hotel (if required)
E) the launch boat cost, if needed and
F) the transportation costs from the following cases and any additional expenses that may occur and we have not included:
i)Port to hotel
ii)Hotel to airport
iii)Port to airport

5- In case we decide to send some spare parts for delivery on board please provide us with the following information:
A) what is the nearest airport where we can send the parts
B) cost per kilo/awb for clearance, transportation, delivery of the spare parts to the vessel
Since we do not have any exact packing details, please give us some examples:
for parcels 5/10/20/50kgs ex Korea and for parcels 5/10/20/50kgs ex foreign countries.
C) time required for all formalities/clearance and delivery to the vessel
D) any specific forwarding procedures
E) exact shipping instructions
F) Launch boat cost, if needed

 

6- Please advise the launch boat cost (per trip or per hr) at anchorage (if required) and whether the same launch boat can be arranged for both deliveries (i.e spares/ stores) and attendees (i.e. crew).

7- Whether 'cash to master' can be advanced in u.s. dollars currency and if so please advise bank charges and delivery expenses if any.

8- In case we decide to send crew mail/ courier from our offices to the vessel please advise if there are extra charges as well as your address for crew mail.

9- In case we decide to deliver lube oil and/ or fuel oil samples to our testing labs overseas, the samples will be sealed and ready for dispatch via paid DHL.
In this respect, please advise us the cost, if any, of landing the samples bottles and arrange the relevant courier service

10- Please advise whether the SSEC can be renewed and if so, please revert with the relevant cost.

11- Any special regulation, documentary requirements or useful information of which we and or master should be aware in advance.

 

Your prompt reply to email: ops@astraship.com will be much appreciated.

 

Thank you very much in advance.

 

Best Regards,

 

Konstantinos Karavas

Disbursement Accounts

Astra Shipmanagement Inc.
6, Vouliagmenis Ave., 16673 Voula,
Athens, Greece
Tel: +30 213 0175 165

E-mail: ops@astraship.com

www.astraship.com

(as agents only)

Prioritizing the wellbeing of our planet and its people.
